---
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import SiteLayout from "../components/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Case Studies"
  description="Production analytics systems, automation workflows, and internal tools architected in live client environments."
  pathname="/case-studies"
  crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Case Studies" }]}
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Production <em>case studies</em>."
    subtitle="Four production systems running inside client analytics environments. Each entry covers the <b>problem</b>, the <b>technical approach</b>, the <b>tools</b>, and the form of <b>evidence</b> available on request."
    crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Case Studies" }]}
  />

  <section class="section wrap first" data-screen-label="Case studies">
    <div class="sec-head rv">
      <div class="sec-head-l">
        <span class="sec-tag"><span class="dot" style="background:var(--terra)"></span>§ Shipped systems</span>
        <h2>Four <em>examples</em>.</h2>
        <p>Each is a real engagement. The system and client names sit behind approvals; supporting diagrams, screenshots, and before/after outputs are available on request.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sec-head-r">/ shipped, not speculative</div>
    </div>

    <div class="codex-grid">
      <article class="cdx feature rv" data-cat="search reporting">
        <div class="cdx-top">
          <div>
            <span class="cdx-tag">/ 01 · Forecasting</span>
            <h3 style="margin-top:6px">Search and traffic <em>forecasting</em> workflows.</h3>
          </div>
          <span class="cdx-status">Live · recurring</span>
        </div>
        <p>Forecasting workflows in BigQuery covering GSC query trends, channel traffic, and monthly reporting cycles. Used by analyst and account teams to flag variance against forecast inside the cycle rather than after it. Stack: BigQuery, Python, GSC API, GA4.</p>
        <div class="cdx-viz">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 600 220" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
            <defs><linearGradient id="case-fill" x1="0" x2="0" y1="0" y2="1"><stop offset="0" stop-color="#c44d2c" stop-opacity=".22"/><stop offset="1" stop-color="#c44d2c" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient></defs>
            <g stroke="#e8e2d2" stroke-dasharray="3 5" fill="none"><line x1="0" y1="60" x2="600" y2="60"/><line x1="0" y1="120" x2="600" y2="120"/><line x1="0" y1="180" x2="600" y2="180"/></g>
            <path class="glow-line" d="M0 170 Q60 150 120 155 T240 130 T360 110" fill="none" stroke="#c44d2c" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M360 110 Q420 90 480 80 T600 50 L600 110 Q540 130 480 140 T360 110 Z" fill="#c89942" fill-opacity=".22"/>
            <path d="M360 110 Q420 100 480 92 T600 70" fill="none" stroke="#c89942" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="5 4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <line x1="360" y1="20" x2="360" y2="200" stroke="#e8e2d2" stroke-dasharray="2 4"/>
            <circle class="pulse-node" cx="360" cy="110" r="5" fill="#c44d2c"/>
            <circle class="ripple" cx="360" cy="110" r="10" fill="none" stroke="#c44d2c" stroke-width="1.5" opacity=".5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="cdx-foot">
          <div class="stack"><span>BigQuery</span><span>Forecasting</span><span>Reporting</span></div>
          <span class="cdx-arrow">Proof on request</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="cdx t-coral rv d1" data-cat="brand detection">
        <div class="cdx-top">
          <div>
            <span class="cdx-tag">/ 02 · Brand monitoring</span>
            <h3 style="margin-top:6px">Sentiment and topic <em>monitoring</em>.</h3>
          </div>
          <span class="cdx-status">Live</span>
        </div>
        <p>LLM-assisted sentiment and topic monitoring across press, review, and social surfaces. The system classifies, deduplicates, and surfaces shifts for the analyst to interpret; nothing is auto-published. Stack: Python, LLM API, structured outputs, BigQuery.</p>
        <div class="cdx-viz">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 180" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
            <defs><linearGradient id="case-arc" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0" stop-color="#d97757"/><stop offset=".5" stop-color="#c89942"/><stop offset="1" stop-color="#7a8f5e"/></linearGradient></defs>
            <path d="M50 140 A100 100 0 0 1 350 140" fill="none" stroke="#e8e2d2" stroke-width="14" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path class="gauge-arc" d="M50 140 A100 100 0 0 1 350 140" fill="none" stroke="url(#case-arc)" stroke-width="14" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <line x1="200" y1="140" x2="270" y2="68" stroke="#1a1714" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <circle class="pulse-node" cx="200" cy="140" r="8" fill="#1a1714"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="cdx-foot">
          <div class="stack"><span>LLM</span><span>NLP</span><span>Monitoring</span></div>
          <span class="cdx-arrow">Evidence pack</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="cdx t-ochre rv d2" data-cat="search brand">
        <div class="cdx-top">
          <div>
            <span class="cdx-tag">/ 03 · AI visibility</span>
            <h3 style="margin-top:6px">AI-mention and search-surface <em>tracking</em>.</h3>
          </div>
          <span class="cdx-status">Operational</span>
        </div>
        <p>Tracking how brands and queries surface across AI Overviews, ChatGPT, Perplexity, and conventional search. Each change is captured with date, prompt, and rendered citation so visibility shifts can be reviewed weeks later.</p>
        <div class="cdx-viz">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 420 190" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
            <g class="tree-grow" fill="none" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round">
              <path d="M184 52 H236" stroke="#c89942" stroke-dasharray="5 4"/>
              <path d="M210 80 V110" stroke="#7a8f5e" stroke-dasharray="5 4"/>
            </g>
            <rect class="pulse-node" x="24" y="24" width="160" height="56" rx="10" fill="#fff5d7" stroke="#c89942"/>
            <rect class="pulse-node" x="236" y="24" width="160" height="56" rx="10" fill="#fde8df" stroke="#c44d2c" style="animation-delay:.5s"/>
            <rect class="pulse-node" x="130" y="110" width="160" height="56" rx="10" fill="#e6ecd9" stroke="#7a8f5e" style="animation-delay:1s"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="cdx-foot">
          <div class="stack"><span>Search</span><span>AI Overviews</span><span>Research</span></div>
          <span class="cdx-arrow">Method notes</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="cdx t-sage rv d3" data-cat="reporting detection">
        <div class="cdx-top">
          <div>
            <span class="cdx-tag">/ 04 · Reporting automation</span>
            <h3 style="margin-top:6px">Automated deck and reporting <em>assembly</em>.</h3>
          </div>
          <span class="cdx-status">Live</span>
        </div>
        <p>Automated assembly of recurring reports and decks from GA4, GSC, and ad-platform data. Replaces a multi-hour manual build with a short analyst review pass. Stack: Python, Google Slides API, BigQuery. Before/after samples available on request.</p>
        <div class="cdx-viz">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 420 190" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
            <rect x="30" y="28" width="130" height="134" rx="12" fill="#fff" stroke="#e8e2d2"/>
            <rect x="180" y="28" width="210" height="134" rx="12" fill="#fafaf5" stroke="#e8e2d2"/>
            <rect x="46" y="44" width="98" height="12" rx="4" fill="#e8e2d2"/>
            <rect class="bar-grow" x="46" y="66" width="78" height="10" rx="4" fill="#f0d690"/>
            <rect x="196" y="44" width="120" height="12" rx="4" fill="#e8e2d2"/>
            <rect class="bar-grow" x="196" y="70" width="170" height="12" rx="4" fill="#fde8df" style="animation-delay:.3s"/>
            <rect class="bar-grow" x="196" y="96" width="160" height="44" rx="8" fill="#e6ecd9" style="animation-delay:.6s"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="cdx-foot">
          <div class="stack"><span>Automation</span><span>Decks</span><span>Client delivery</span></div>
          <span class="cdx-arrow">Approved samples</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section wrap" data-screen-label="Proof notes">
    <div class="sec-head rv">
      <div class="sec-head-l">
        <span class="sec-tag"><span class="dot" style="background:var(--moss)"></span>§ How the evidence is held</span>
        <h2>Evidence <em>available</em> on request.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="sec-head-r"><a href="/evidence">Full evidence index →</a></div>
    </div>

    <div class="bento">
      <a class="cap feature rv" href="/evidence">
        <span class="cap-num">/ 01 · Evidence index</span>
        <div class="cap-icon"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6"><path d="M7 4 H17 A2 2 0 0 1 19 6 V18 A2 2 0 0 1 17 20 H7 A2 2 0 0 1 5 18 V6 A2 2 0 0 1 7 4 Z"/><path d="M8 9 H16"/><path d="M8 13 H16"/><path d="M8 17 H13"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Each case study has <em>supporting documents</em>.</h3>
        <p>Approved screenshots, diagrams, methodology notes, before/after reporting outputs, and recommendation context are catalogued in the evidence index and shared on request.</p>
        <span class="cap-go">Open evidence →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="cap rv d1 t-ochre" href="/recognition">
        <span class="cap-num">/ 02</span>
        <div class="cap-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6"><path d="M12 3 L20 7 V13 C20 17 16.5 20.5 12 22 C7.5 20.5 4 17 4 13 V7 Z"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Recognition and <em>peer review</em>.</h3>
        <span class="cap-go">Recognition →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="cap rv d2 t-coral" href="/publications">
        <span class="cap-num">/ 03</span>
        <div class="cap-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="16" rx="2"/><line x1="3" y1="9" x2="21" y2="9"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Publications and <em>archive proof</em>.</h3>
        <span class="cap-go">Publications →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="cap rv d3 t-sage" href="/testimonials">
        <span class="cap-num">/ 04</span>
        <div class="cap-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6"><path d="M21 12c0 4.5-4 8-9 8a10 10 0 0 1-4-.8L3 21l1.4-3.4A8 8 0 0 1 3 12c0-4.5 4-8 9-8s9 3.5 9 8z"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Testimonials and <em>recommendation context</em>.</h3>
        <span class="cap-go">Testimonials →</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
